ex tasks where human supervision\nis unreliable, RLHF may no longer be the best use of human comparison feedback;\ninstead, it is better to direct feedback towards improving the training data\nrather than continually training the model. Our code and data are available at\nhttps://github.com/helloelwin/iterative-label-refinement.\n</summary>\n    <author>\n      <name>Yaowen Ye</name>\n    </author>\n    <author>\n      <name>Cassidy Laidlaw</name>\n    </author>\n    <author>\n      <name>Jacob Steinhardt</name>\n    </author>\n    <arxiv:comment xmlns:arxiv=\"http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom\">22 pages, 10 figures</arxiv:comment>\n    <link href=\"http://arxiv.org/abs/2501.07886v1\" rel=\"alternate\" type=\"text/html\"/>\n    <link title=\"pdf\" href=\"http://arxiv.org/pdf/2501.07886v1\" rel=\"related\" type=\"application/pdf\"/>\n    <arxiv:primary_category xmlns:arxiv=\"http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom\" term=\"cs.LG\" scheme=\"http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom\"/>\n    <category term=\"cs.LG\" scheme=\"http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom\"/>\n    <category term=\"cs.AI\" scheme=\"http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom\"/>\n    <category term=\"cs.CL\" scheme=\"http://arxiv.org/schemas/atom\"/>\n  </entry>\n  <entry>\n    <id>http://arxiv.org/abs/2005.04994v2</id>\n    <updated>2020-08-19T10:20:50Z</updated>\n    <published>2020-05-11T10:59:33Z</published>\n    <title>From entropic to energetic barriers in glassy dynamics: The\n  Barrat-M\u00e9zard trap model on sparse networks</title>\n    <summary>  Trap models describe glassy dynamics as a stochastic process on a network of\nconfigurations representing local energy minima. We study within this class the\nparadigmatic Barrat-M\\'ezard model, which has Glauber transition rates. Our\nfocus is on the effects of the network connectivity, where we go beyond the\nusual mean field (fully connected) approximation and consider sparse networks,\nspecifically random regular graphs. We obtain the spectral density of\nrelaxation rates of the master